== Sweet Potato ==

Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @sweet potato{1%unit} into 1cm chunks (no need to peel), then pop it onto a
large #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, sprinkle over the @roasted spice and herb blend{1%sachet},
season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden and tender, ~{18-20%mins}.
Turn halfway through.

== Bulgur Tabbouleh ==

Meanwhile, peel and grate the @garlic clove{2}(peeled) (or use a garlic press).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot,
add the garlic and fry for ~{30%seconds}, then stir in the @bulgur wheat{120%grams}
and cook for another ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @vegetable stock paste{15%grams} and @water for the bulgur{220%milliliters},
then bring to the boil. Simmer for ~{1%minute}, then pop a #lid{} on the pan and
remove from the heat.

Leave to the side for ~{12-15%mins} or until ready to serve.

== Pickled Carrot ==

Meanwhile, cut the @lemon{1%unit} into wedges.

Trim and peel the @carrot{1%unit}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the
length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Pop the carrot ribbons into a #medium bowl{}. Squeeze in some lemon juice and add
the @sugar for the pickle{1%tsp}.

Season with @salt{}, mix together well, then set aside to pickle.

== Harissa Yoghurt ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine the @Greek style natural yoghurt{75%grams} with half
the @harissa paste{50%grams} (add less if you'd prefer things milder). Set aside.

== Assembly ==

Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1%bunch} (stalks and all).

Once the bulgur is ready, fluff it up with a #fork{} and stir in the parsley and
remaining harissa paste.

Add a good squeeze of lemon juice and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Set your
tabbouleh aside for now.

Just before the sweet potato is ready, place the @ready to eat falafels{171%grams}
on a #plate{} and microwave, 800W: ~{75%secs} / 900W: ~{45%secs} / 1000W: ~{30%secs}.

> If you don't have a microwave, place the falafels onto a baking tray and bake on
> the top shelf until golden brown, about 5-8 mins.

Once ready, drizzle the @honey{2%tbsp} over the falafels and turn so they're nicely
glazed.

== Serving ==

Share your tabbouleh between your serving bowls.

Top the tabbouleh with your glazed falafels, roast sweet potato and pickled carrot
in separate sections.

Drizzle the harissa yoghurt over the falafels and sweet potato to finish.

Serve with any remaining lemon wedges for squeezing over.

Enjoy!